rComments: Really nice person and he does explain the topics well. Don't be afraid to ask questions because he just genuinely wants to help. Slides are 10/10.

One of my favourite professors at the University of Toronto. His course isn't entirely difficult. His passion for Canadian politics is evident in his lectures. Good sense of humour and extremely kind. Overall, good prof to have in one's university experience

Had helpful slides, brought in speakers who work in politics so it wasn't always monotonous, and genuinely tried to make the course content (which wasn't too difficult) interesting.  He also comes off as a genuinely kind and approachable person. Recommended.
Professor Rheault was an amazing professor, with even better slides to boast. Really went slow on the more difficult topics and explained the content well. Was readily available to talk too
